<HEADLINE>
Official: Pakistan Christian innocent of blasphemy
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
ISLAMABAD 2010-11-22 12:58:56 UTC
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A government minister investigating the case of a Pakistani Christian woman sentenced to death for blasphemy against Islam says he believes she is innocent.
</P>
<P>
Minister for Minority Affairs Shahbaz Bhatti said Monday he is confident Pakistan's president will pardon Asia Bibi because she was falsely accused.
</P>
<P>
The 45-year-old was sentenced Nov. 8 to hang for insulting the Prophet Muhammad.
</P>
<P>
The mother of five has spent 1 1/2 years in prison.
</P>
<P>
Bibi says the case is the result of a personal dispute with some Muslim women over whether they could share the same water bowl.
</P>
<P>
President Asif Ali Zardari has asked Bhatti to submit a review of the case
</P>
<P>
Last week Pope Benedict XVI appealed for Bibi's release.
</P>
</TEXT>
